  90:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     Use Function HAL_UART_RegisterCallback() to register a user callback.
  91:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     Function HAL_UART_RegisterCallback() allows to register following callbacks:
  92:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) TxHalfCpltCallback        : Tx Half Complete Callback.
  93:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) TxCpltCallback            : Tx Complete Callback.
  94:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) RxHalfCpltCallback        : Rx Half Complete Callback.
  95:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) RxCpltCallback            : Rx Complete Callback.
  96:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) ErrorCallback             : Error Callback.
  97:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) AbortCpltCallback         : Abort Complete Callback.
  98:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) AbortTransmitCpltCallback : Abort Transmit Complete Callback.
  99:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) AbortReceiveCpltCallback  : Abort Receive Complete Callback.
 100:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) WakeupCallback            : Wakeup Callback.
 101:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback           : UART MspInit.
 102:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback         : UART MspDeInit.
 103:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     This function takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle, the Callback ID
 104:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     and a pointer to the user callback function.
 105:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c **** 
 106:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     [..]
 107:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     Use function HAL_UART_UnRegisterCallback() to reset a callback to the default
 108:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     weak function.
 109:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     HAL_UART_UnRegisterCallback() takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle,
 110:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     and the Callback ID.
 111:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     This function allows to reset following callbacks:
 112:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) TxHalfCpltCallback        : Tx Half Complete Callback.
 113:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) TxCpltCallback            : Tx Complete Callback.
 114:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) RxHalfCpltCallback        : Rx Half Complete Callback.
 115:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) RxCpltCallback            : Rx Complete Callback.
 116:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) ErrorCallback             : Error Callback.
 117:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) AbortCpltCallback         : Abort Complete Callback.
 118:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) AbortTransmitCpltCallback : Abort Transmit Complete Callback.
 119:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) AbortReceiveCpltCallback  : Abort Receive Complete Callback.
 120:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) WakeupCallback            : Wakeup Callback.
 121:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback           : UART MspInit.
 122:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback         : UART MspDeInit.
 123:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c **** 
 124:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     [..]
 125:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     For specific callback RxEventCallback, use dedicated registration/reset functions:
 126:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     respectively HAL_UART_RegisterRxEventCallback() , HAL_UART_UnRegisterRxEventCallback().
 127:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c **** 
 128:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     [..]
 129:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     By default, after the HAL_UART_Init() and when the state is HAL_UART_STATE_RESET
 130:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions:
 131:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     examples HAL_UART_TxCpltCallback(), HAL_UART_RxHalfCpltCallback().
 132:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit functions that are respectively
 133:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     reset to the legacy weak functions in the HAL_UART_Init()
 134:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     and HAL_UART_DeInit() only when these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 135:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     If not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the HAL_UART_Init() and HAL_UART_DeInit()
 136:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand).
 137:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c **** 
 138:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     [..]
 139:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_UART_STATE_READY state only.
 140:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     Exception done MspInit/MspDeInit that can be registered/unregistered
 141:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     in HAL_UART_STATE_READY or HAL_UART_STATE_RESET state, thus registered (user)
 142:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
 143:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 144:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     using HAL_UART_RegisterCallback() before calling HAL_UART_DeInit()
 145:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     or HAL_UART_Init() function.
 146:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c **** 
