 230:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****             ##### Initialization and Configuration functions #####
 231:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****  ===============================================================================
 232:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     [..]
 233:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     This subsection provides a set of functions allowing to initialize the USARTx or the UARTy
 234:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     in asynchronous mode.
 235:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****       (+) For the asynchronous mode the parameters below can be configured:
 236:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) Baud Rate
 237:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) Word Length
 238:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) Stop Bit
 239:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) Parity: If the parity is enabled, then the MSB bit of the data written
 240:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****              in the data register is transmitted but is changed by the parity bit.
 241:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) Hardware flow control
 242:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) Receiver/transmitter modes
 243:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) Over Sampling Method
 244:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) One-Bit Sampling Method
 245:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****       (+) For the asynchronous mode, the following advanced features can be configured as well:
 246:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) TX and/or RX pin level inversion
 247:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) data logical level inversion
 248:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) RX and TX pins swap
 249:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) RX overrun detection disabling
 250:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) DMA disabling on RX error
 251:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) MSB first on communication line
 252:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) auto Baud rate detection
 253:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     [..]
 254:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     The HAL_UART_Init(), HAL_HalfDuplex_Init(), HAL_LIN_Init()and HAL_MultiProcessor_Init()API
 255:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     follow respectively the UART asynchronous, UART Half duplex, UART LIN mode
 256:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     and UART multiprocessor mode configuration procedures (details for the procedures
 257:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     are available in reference manual).
