 991:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     This subsection provides a set of functions allowing to manage the UART asynchronous
 992:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     and Half duplex data transfers.
 993:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c **** 
 994:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (#) There are two modes of transfer:
 995:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****        (++) Blocking mode: The communication is performed in polling mode.
 996:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****             The HAL status of all data processing is returned by the same function
 997:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****             after finishing transfer.
 998:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****        (++) Non-Blocking mode: The communication is performed using Interrupts
 999:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****             or DMA, These API's return the HAL status.
1000:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****             The end of the data processing will be indicated through the
1001:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****             dedicated UART IRQ when using Interrupt mode or the DMA IRQ when
ARM GAS  C:\Users\Tilen\AppData\Local\Temp\cc9NLyjk.s 			page 19


1002:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****             using DMA mode.
1003:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****             The HAL_UART_TxCpltCallback(), HAL_UART_RxCpltCallback() user callbacks
1004:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****             will be executed respectively at the end of the transmit or Receive process
1005:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****             The HAL_UART_ErrorCallback()user callback will be executed when a communication error i
1006:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c **** 
1007:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (#) Blocking mode API's are :
1008:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) HAL_UART_Transmit()
1009:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) HAL_UART_Receive()
1010:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c **** 
1011:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (#) Non-Blocking mode API's with Interrupt are :
