1035:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) HAL_UART_AbortTransmit_IT()
1036:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) HAL_UART_AbortReceive_IT()
1037:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c **** 
1038:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (#) For Abort services based on interrupts (HAL_UART_Abortxxx_IT), a set of Abort Complete Call
1039:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) HAL_UART_AbortCpltCallback()
1040:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) HAL_UART_AbortTransmitCpltCallback()
1041:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) HAL_UART_AbortReceiveCpltCallback()
1042:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c **** 
1043:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (#) A Rx Event Reception Callback (Rx event notification) is available for Non_Blocking modes o
1044:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         reception services:
1045:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) HAL_UARTEx_RxEventCallback()
1046:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c **** 
1047:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (#) Wakeup from Stop mode Callback:
1048:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) HAL_UARTEx_WakeupCallback()
1049:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c **** 
1050:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****     (#) In Non-Blocking mode transfers, possible errors are split into 2 categories.
1051:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****         Errors are handled as follows :
1052:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****        (++) Error is considered as Recoverable and non blocking : Transfer could go till end, but e
1053:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****             to be evaluated by user : this concerns Frame Error, Parity Error or Noise Error
1054:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****             in Interrupt mode reception .
1055:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****             Received character is then retrieved and stored in Rx buffer, Error code is set to allo
1056:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****             to identify error type, and HAL_UART_ErrorCallback() user callback is executed.
1057:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****             Transfer is kept ongoing on UART side.
1058:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****             If user wants to abort it, Abort services should be called by user.
ARM GAS  C:\Users\Tilen\AppData\Local\Temp\cc9NLyjk.s 			page 20


1059:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****        (++) Error is considered as Blocking : Transfer could not be completed properly and is abort
1060:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****             This concerns Overrun Error In Interrupt mode reception and all errors in DMA mode.
1061:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****             Error code is set to allow user to identify error type, and HAL_UART_ErrorCallback()
1062:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_uart.c ****             user callback is executed.
